<BaseLayout
  title="Affiliate & Commercial Relationships — Arrivly"
  description="How Arrivly makes money and why commission never influences our recommendations. Disclosed per ACCC guidelines.">

  <article class="prose max-w-[760px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-8 pt-12 pb-16 sm:pt-20 sm:pb-24">
    <h1>Affiliate &amp; Commercial Relationships</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: May 2026</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>The short version</strong>
      Some links on Arrivly earn us a small commission if you sign up. This never changes what we recommend.
    </div>

    <h2>How we make money</h2>
    <p>Arrivly is free to use. We earn revenue through affiliate commissions — when you click a link to a provider and sign up for their service, we may receive a payment from that provider.</p>
    <p>This is a standard practice for comparison websites. It is how we pay for the time spent researching, verifying, and maintaining this site.</p>

    <h2>What this means for you</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You pay the same price whether you come through our link or go direct</li>
      <li>We never mark up prices</li>
      <li>Commissions come from the provider's marketing budget, not from your pocket</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Does commission affect our recommendations?</h2>
    <p>No. Here is why we are confident saying that:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>We rank by fit, not fee.</strong> Our recommendation engine scores plans based on how well they match your answers. Commission rate is not a factor in the scoring.</li>
      <li><strong>We include plans with no affiliate program.</strong> If a plan is genuinely good for users, we include it even if we earn nothing from it.</li>
      <li><strong>We show our data sources.</strong> Every plan shows when it was verified and from where. You can check our work.</li>
      <li><strong>We disclose limitations honestly.</strong> We tell you when Lycamobile data needs verification. We tell you no SIM includes unlimited Nepal calls. We do not hide inconvenient facts to protect commissions.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Which providers have affiliate relationships</h2>
    <p>We are currently applying for affiliate programs with the following providers. This page will be updated when those applications are approved:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Boost Mobile (via Commission Factory)</li>
      <li>Lebara (via Commission Factory)</li>
      <li>Felix Mobile (direct / Commission Factory)</li>
      <li>amaysim (via Commission Factory)</li>
      <li>Lycamobile (direct)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Plans marked with a small "↗" icon link to the provider's site. Some of these are affiliate links.</p>

    <h2>Australian disclosure requirements</h2>
    <p>This disclosure is made in accordance with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Australian Consumer Law (Competition and Consumer Act 2010)</li>
      <li>ACCC guidelines on comparison websites and influencer marketing (2023)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Under Australian Consumer Law, businesses must not engage in misleading or deceptive conduct. Undisclosed commercial relationships in comparison or review content may constitute misleading conduct.</p>

    <h2>Questions</h2>
    <p>If you have questions about our commercial relationships, email us at:<br />
      <strong>[YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS]</strong></p>
  </article>

